mermaid-rs-remote-renderer
==========================

This product is a derivative work based on the upstream open-source project
**mermaid-rs-renderer** (https://github.com/1jehuang/mermaid-rs-renderer),
which is distributed under the MIT License.

The upstream library performs all of the heavy lifting: parsing Mermaid
syntax, computing layout, and rendering SVG. This project (the
"remote-renderer") wraps that library behind an HTTP server that exposes
a kroki / mermaid.ink-compatible GET endpoint, plus production hardening
(structured logging, per-IP rate limiting, concurrency caps, body size and
render timeouts, optional token gate, and Docker/CI tooling).

The original `LICENSE` file from the upstream project is preserved and
applies to the underlying library code. The MIT License text in this
repository's `LICENSE` file covers both the upstream copyright holders and
contributions made in this fork.

